==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*folkom'' ‘people’, from ''*fulka-'' ‘crowd, army’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[folk]], Old Saxon ''folc'', Old Dutch ''folk'' (Dutch [[volk]]), Old High German ''folc'' (German [[Volk]]), Old Norse [[folk]] ‘people, army’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/folk/}}

===Noun===
'''folc''' ''n'' (plural '''folc''')
# [[people]], [[nation]], [[race]]
# [[army]]
# ''(in plural)'' people in general

